<title>HONG KONG: Burglar chooses wrong building to rob.</title>
<headline>Burglar chooses wrong building to rob.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-04-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>A newly arrived illegal immigrant from China chose the wrong building to burgle -- he broke into a Hong Kong police officer's flat.</p>
<p>A police spokesman said on Monday Constable Cheung Sui-chung arrested the 25-year-old burglar and recovered his wallet containing his police warrant card and more than HK$2,500 ($320) in cash.</p>
<p>(US$1=HK$7.78)</p>
